snippet.textDisplay:
So not really surprising that the Seahawks took this one. Three years in a row the Eagles have been getting injured and the injuries have gotten worse and more frequent. You can’t say their all accidents. They need to learn to prevent more of these if they want to enter playoff games with the personnel needed to compete. They themselves dug this hole, and it didn’t help that Jadeveon Clowney cheap shot Carson Wentz out of the game. I’m not saying the outcome should be changed, but he should at least be fined. He has a well-documented dirty hatred of the Eagles and he needs to pay for it.



So the Eagles hardly had the ability to take on the Seahawks defense. They were outmatched. Couldn’t run, couldn’t pass. Didn’t even score double digits.



With the Seahawks offense matching up against the Eagles defense, nothing was that surprising. They couldn’t run the ball because Fletcher Cox was demolishing their interior. DK Metcalf ran all over the Eagles secondary and Russell Wilson was hitting him in stride all day. Low scoring game, but an effective Seahawks win.
